  "accepted_findings": [
    "The fresh V18 baseline reproduces both V16 alpha4 hashes exactly, preserving the diagnostic control.",
    "The isolated-review fill changes 43.36 percent of guide-seat pixels and 30.17 percent of river-eye pixels, proving that the transient direct lights affect the loaded corridor scene.",
    "The crown-only mask records only a 2-3 level RGB lift under direct fill and remains predominantly dark in both views.",
    "The 3.10 skylight-only captures are byte-identical to baseline under the current offscreen corridor path and provide no visual correction."
  ],
  "rejection_reasons": [
    "The direct-fill treatment brightens terrain and water much more than foliage and would wash out the valley before restoring readable crowns.",
    "After direct fill, 70.86 percent of guide-seat and 82.68 percent of river-eye restored-crown pixels remain below the dark threshold.",
    "The skylight treatment produces no pixel change and cannot justify a saved photometry change.",
    "Four-times alpha still produces visually saturated, non-leaf-shaped crown masses and remains promotion-ineligible."
  ],
  "next_iteration_requirements": [
    "Hold the saved corridor light rig fixed and test a two-times LeafBaseColorScale override independently from a neutral-white LeafTransmissionTint override.",
    "Include a combined reflectance-plus-transmission control only to detect interaction; do not promote any diagnostic override automatically.",
    "Use the same restored-crown mask to measure whether color improves in foliage rather than merely brightening terrain or water.",
    "After choosing a physically plausible leaf response, reduce opacity amplification and recover leaf-edge breakup before ecology expansion."
  ]
